String in java:
String is the class names for strings.
It contains a sequence of characters.
String->Object

String are immutable in java->

String in java are immutable:
A string value once created,can not changed.
if method is called on string object,it returns a new object and will not 
modify the original object.

All string literals are stored n String constant pool.
if jvm finds a string literal,

new operator->a new object is created on heap memory location.

Imp.
String ,StringBuffer ,StringBuilder.






package javacore;

import java.util.Scanner;

public class HelloWorld {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		int[] numbers=new int[100];//creation of an array
		numbers[0]=10;
		numbers[1]=20;
		numbers[2]=30;
		numbers[3]=40;
		numbers[4]=50;
		
		for(int i=0;i<5;i++) {
			System.out.println(numbers[i]);//10 20 30 40 50
		}

	
	}
}
